      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1069">
               <p>Son of <persName>Martin Horbery</persName>, the vicar of <placeName>Haxey,
                     Lincolnshire</placeName> (just south of <placeName>Epworth</placeName>),
                  Matthew had matriculated at Lincoln College in <date when="1726-05">May
                     1726</date>. He received his <seg ana="degree">BA</seg> in <date when="1730-01"
                     >Jan. 1730</date> and was ordained deacon in <date when="1730-12">Dec</date>.
                  of that year. He was frequently in <placeName>Epworth</placeName> between <date
                     when="1731-01">Jan. 1731</date> and <date when="1733-03">Mar. 1733</date> (when
                  he was ordained priest) perhaps serving as <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2188.xml"/>Samuel Wesley Sr</persName>.&apos;s curate.
                  Several Wesley family members sought to match him with <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2182.xml"/>Martha</persName>, but she was not so
                  inclined. On <date when="1733-12-21">Dec. 21, 1733</date> he officiated at the
                  marriage of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2183.xml"/>Mary Wesley</persName>
                  to <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2227.xml"/>John Whitelamb</persName>.
                  Horbery&apos;s parents died early, leaving him a comfortable estate that allowed
                  him to become Lincolnshire Fellow of Magdalene College,
                     <placeName>Oxford</placeName>. He went on to earn both his <seg ana="degree"
                     >BD</seg> and <seg ana="degree">DD</seg> degrees and serve as a prebend, then
                  canon, of <placeName>Litchfield</placeName> cathedral. See <hi rend="italic"
                     >Alumni Oxonienses</hi>; <hi rend="italic">CCEd</hi>, and <hi rend="italic"
                     >ODNB</hi>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
